&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our service users are looking for a Clinical/Counselling Psychologist &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span&gt;Who can you make real positive difference for people suffering with chronic pain.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be valued member within our multi-disciplinary Chronic Pain Management Service (CPMS) for the population of South East and East Staffordshire (Lichfield, Tamworth and Burton On Trent). Although, this post is a full time post, part time working hours are open for discussion. We also have scope to offer a preceptorship opportunity, with a Band 7 post having an agreed progression to Band 8a.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for providing input into the Pain Management Programme, as well as offering individual psychological input. Approaches such as CBT, ACT and compassion focused approaches are currently used within the service. There are regular specialty meetings with the wider Physical Health teams, as well as opportunities to link with other psychologists at the annual Psychological Services Conference. As a chronic pain service, we have regular in-service training and staff development is valued and encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ashish Khiloshiya, Clinical Lead CPMS 07933683383&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr. Nita Baker : Consultant neuropsychologist and head of physical health psychology team nita.baker@mpft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
